  <h1>Public <em>code</em>.</h1>
  <p>Most production work is private — client analytics systems, agency automation, proprietary reporting. Public repos are <b>deliberate examples</b> that demonstrate engineering approach.</p>
</header>

<section class="section wrap first" data-screen-label="Terminal">
  <div class="terminal rv">
    <div class="terminal-bar">
      <div class="dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
      <div class="ttl">~/tayyub-ai · git · 4 repos</div>
    </div>
    <div class="terminal-body">
      <div class="tline typing"><span class="prompt">$</span><span class="cmd">whoami</span></div>
      <div class="term-out fade d1">tayyub-ai — public engineering profile<br /><a href="https://github.com/tayyub-ai" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">github.com/tayyub-ai ↗</a></div>

      <div class="tline typing t2"><span class="prompt">$</span><span class="cmd">ls -la public/</span></div>
      <div class="term-out fade d2">
        <span class="repo"><b>analytics-audit-examples</b> <i>· open utility scripts &amp; example checks for GA4 / consent / tagging audit logic</i><br /><span class="tag py">python</span><span class="tag api">ga4 admin api</span></span>
        <span class="repo"><b>gsc-bigquery-notebooks</b> <i>· notebooks for joining GSC exports to BigQuery, with AI-Overview tagging samples used in the visibility research</i><br /><span class="tag py">python</span><span class="tag bq">bigquery</span></span>
        <span class="repo"><b>pptx-report-engine</b> <i>· reference scaffold for automated PowerPoint reporting — the public-safe version of the agency tooling</i><br /><span class="tag py">python-pptx</span><span class="tag sql">templating</span></span>
        <span class="repo"><b>forecasting-sketches</b> <i>· small, well-documented forecasting / anomaly-detection examples illustrating the engineering style of the larger private systems</i><br /><span class="tag py">prophet</span><span class="tag py">sklearn</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="tline typing" style="animation-delay:3.4s"><span class="prompt">$</span><span class="cmd">cat NOTE.txt</span></div>
      <div class="term-out fade d3">
        <div class="term-note">
          ⚠ <b>I don't lean on GitHub stars as recognition.</b> The point of this page is <b>code as evidence</b> — that I write production-grade Python, document it, and understand the systems I describe. The serious systems are private to clients; the public set is shareable surface area.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tline"><span class="prompt">$</span><span class="term-cursor"></span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

